  "bm4j": {
    "text": "The buttons demonstrate how to use 'hover' and 'hover' with 'transition'. In order to use those, css must become a compound object which generates a style sheet for the widget. Use 'default' or just empty quotes for the part that is the ID selector for the widget. Then use a 'hover' key to specify the hover properties.",
    "id": "bm4j",
    "x": 60,
    "z": 10659,
    "width": 300,
    "movable": false,
    "y": 650
  },
  "bm5j": {
    "text": "This widget uses default css for its normal state, so nothing is specified in the 'default' selector. But then it uses 'hover' and 'after' selectors to create a tooltip effect.",
